statement.p:
Simplify the rational expression
\frac{12 a b^{4}}{21 b^{6}}
in the form \frac{A}{B}.

Perform the indicated operation.  Note that the denominators
are the same.  Simplify the result, if possible.
\frac{y^{2}}{y^{2}-25} + \frac{25-10y}{y^{2}-25}

solution.p:
The denominators are equal.  Add the numerators. Factor and reduce.
\begin{aligned}
\frac{y^{2}}{y^{2}-25} + \frac{25-10y}{y^{2}-25}  \amp  = \frac{y^2 + 25 - 10 y}{y^2 - 25} \amp  \\
                \amp  = \frac{y^2 - 10 y + 25}{y^2 - 25}  \amp  \\
                \amp  = \frac{(y - 5)(y - 5)}{(y + 5)(y - 5)} \amp  \mbox{Reduce common factors}\\
                \amp  = \frac{y-5}{y+5}
\end{aligned}

statement.p:
Simplify the complex fraction
{
\frac{\displaystyle \; \frac{1}{x}+\frac{5}{x^2}\;}{\displaystyle \frac{10}{y}+\frac{11}{y^2}}
}
in the form \frac{A}{B}.

Simplify the expression
\frac{5 x^3-8 x^2-4 x}{4 x^2-12 x+8}
and give your answer in the form of
\frac{f(x)}{g(x)}
where f(x) and g(x) are polynomials with no common factors.

Select all expressions that are equivalent to 
\frac{x-2}{7 x} \cdot  \frac{x}{x^2-4}
There may be more than one correct answer.

solution.p:
Subtracting fractions is easy when they have a common denominator, so first get a common denominator, then subtract:    
\displaystyle{\begin{aligned}
    \frac{1}{x+5}-\frac{1}{x+6} 
    \amp =\frac{x+6}{(x+5)(x+6)} 
     -\frac{x+5}{(x+5)(x+6)}\\
    \amp =\frac{(x+6)-(x+5)}{(x+5)(x+6)}\\
    \amp =\frac{1}{(x+5)(x+6)} 
    \end{aligned} }

statement.p:
Simplify the complex fraction
1+\frac{\displaystyle \; 1 \;}{\displaystyle  \; 1+\frac{1}{\displaystyle \; 1+ \frac{1}{x}\;}}
in the form \frac{A}{B}.

Simplify the rational expression
\frac{7(xy^{5}+y^{6})}{x^2-y^2}
in the form \frac{A}{B}.

Simplify the rational expression
\frac{1}{x^{4}} + \frac{1}{x^{6}}
in the form \frac{A}{B}.  Express the final result in a single fraction using positive exponents only.

solution.p:
The LCD is 3x5.
\begin{aligned} 
11 - \frac{5}{15x} \amp  = \frac{11}{1} \cdot \frac{3x5}{3x5} - \frac{5}{15x} \\
          \amp  = \frac{33x55}{3x5} - \frac{5}{3x5} \\
          \amp  = \frac{33x+50}{3x+5}               
\end{aligned}

statement.p:
Simplify the expression
\sqrt{192 y^{4}}
into the simplest radical form A \sqrt{C}, where A and C are either integers or monomials.  Assume y\geq 0.

Express the number
\left( \frac{2^{-4}}{5^{-2}} \right)^{-1}
as a reduced fraction.

Assume that a and b represent positive real numbers.  Simplify the expression
-5 \sqrt{28 a^{7} b^{2}}
into the simplest radical form A \sqrt{C}, where A and C are either integers or monomials.

Change the radical
\sqrt{\frac{3}{8}\;}
into simplest radical form \frac{A}{B} \sqrt{C}, where A, B, and C are all integers.

