BEGIN_PGML Consier the equation
[``` \sin(x+y) = \sin x + \sin y ```]
Which of the following statements are true, and which are false?
a. The above equation holds for all values of [`x`] and [`y\text{.}`] [_]{$popup1}{5}
a. The above equation holds for at least some value(s) of [`x`] and [`y\text{.}`] [_]{$popup2}{5}
a. The above equation holds for at least some non-zero value(s) of [`x`] and [`y\text{.}`] [_]{$popup3}{5}
a. The above equation is a trigonometric identity. [_]{$popup4}{5}
END_PGML
